47// Finds a stream based on target's Primary SSRC or RIDs.
48// This struct is used in BaseChannel::UpdateLocalStreams_w.
49struct StreamFinder {
50 explicit StreamFinder(const StreamParams* target) : target_(target) {
51 RTC_DCHECK(target);
52 }
53
54 bool operator()(const StreamParams& sp) const {
55 if (target_->has_ssrcs() && sp.has_ssrcs()) {
56 return sp.has_ssrc(target_->first_ssrc());
57 }
58
59 if (!target_->has_rids() && !sp.has_rids()) {
60 return false;
61 }
62
63 const std::vector<RidDescription>& target_rids = target_->rids();
64 const std::vector<RidDescription>& source_rids = sp.rids();
65 if (source_rids.size() != target_rids.size()) {
66 return false;
67 }
68
69 // Check that all RIDs match.
70 return std::equal(source_rids.begin(), source_rids.end(),
71 target_rids.begin(),
72 [](const RidDescription& lhs, const RidDescription& rhs) {
73 return lhs.rid == rhs.rid;
74 });
75 }
76
77 const StreamParams* target_;
78};
79
80} // namespace

82static void SafeSetError(const std::string& message, std::string* error_desc) {
83 if (error_desc) {
84 *error_desc = message;
85 }
86}

88template <class Codec>
89void RtpParametersFromMediaDescription(
90 const MediaContentDescriptionImpl<Codec>* desc,
91 const RtpHeaderExtensions& extensions,
92 bool is_stream_active,
93 RtpParameters<Codec>* params) {
94 params->is_stream_active = is_stream_active;
95 params->codecs = desc->codecs();
96 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11513): See if we really need
97 // rtp_header_extensions_set() and remove it if we don't.
98 if (desc->rtp_header_extensions_set()) {
99 params->extensions = extensions;
100 }
101 params->rtcp.reduced_size = desc->rtcp_reduced_size();
102 params->rtcp.remote_estimate = desc->remote_estimate();
103}
104
105template <class Codec>
106void RtpSendParametersFromMediaDescription(
107 const MediaContentDescriptionImpl<Codec>* desc,
108 const RtpHeaderExtensions& extensions,
109 bool is_stream_active,
110 RtpSendParameters<Codec>* send_params) {
111 RtpParametersFromMediaDescription(desc, extensions, is_stream_active,
112 send_params);
113 send_params->max_bandwidth_bps = desc->bandwidth();
114 send_params->extmap_allow_mixed = desc->extmap_allow_mixed();
115}

117BaseChannel::BaseChannel(rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
118 rtc::Thread* network_thread,
119 rtc::Thread* signaling_thread,
120 std::unique_ptr<MediaChannel> media_channel,
121 const std::string& content_name,
122 bool srtp_required,
123 webrtc::CryptoOptions crypto_options,
124 UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator)
125 : worker_thread_(worker_thread),
126 network_thread_(network_thread),
127 signaling_thread_(signaling_thread),
128 alive_(PendingTaskSafetyFlag::Create()),
129 content_name_(content_name),
130 srtp_required_(srtp_required),
131 crypto_options_(crypto_options),
132 media_channel_(std::move(media_channel)),
133 ssrc_generator_(ssrc_generator) {
134 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
135 RTC_DCHECK(ssrc_generator_);
136 demuxer_criteria_.mid = content_name;
137 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Created channel: " << ToString();
138}
139
140BaseChannel::~BaseChannel() {
141 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "BaseChannel::~BaseChannel");
142 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
143
144 // Eats any outstanding messages or packets.
145 alive_->SetNotAlive();
146 // The media channel is destroyed at the end of the destructor, since it
147 // is a std::unique_ptr. The transport channel (rtp_transport) must outlive
148 // the media channel.
149}
150
151std::string BaseChannel::ToString() const {
152 rtc::StringBuilder sb;
153 sb << "{mid: " << content_name_;
154 if (media_channel_) {
155 sb << ", media_type: " << MediaTypeToString(media_channel_->media_type());
156 }
157 sb << "}";
158 return sb.Release();
159}
160
161bool BaseChannel::ConnectToRtpTransport() {
162 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_transport_);
163 RTC_DCHECK(media_channel());
164
165 // We don't need to call OnDemuxerCriteriaUpdatePending/Complete because
166 // there's no previous criteria to worry about.
167 bool result = rtp_transport_->RegisterRtpDemuxerSink(demuxer_criteria_, this);
168 if (result) {
169 previous_demuxer_criteria_ = demuxer_criteria_;
170 } else {
171 previous_demuxer_criteria_ = {};
172 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to set up demuxing for " << ToString();
173 return false;
174 }
175 rtp_transport_->SignalReadyToSend.connect(
176 this, &BaseChannel::OnTransportReadyToSend);
177 rtp_transport_->SignalNetworkRouteChanged.connect(
178 this, &BaseChannel::OnNetworkRouteChanged);
179 rtp_transport_->SignalWritableState.connect(this,
180 &BaseChannel::OnWritableState);
181 rtp_transport_->SignalSentPacket.connect(this,
182 &BaseChannel::SignalSentPacket_n);
183 return true;
184}
185
186void BaseChannel::DisconnectFromRtpTransport() {
187 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_transport_);
188 RTC_DCHECK(media_channel());
189 rtp_transport_->UnregisterRtpDemuxerSink(this);
190 rtp_transport_->SignalReadyToSend.disconnect(this);
191 rtp_transport_->SignalNetworkRouteChanged.disconnect(this);
192 rtp_transport_->SignalWritableState.disconnect(this);
193 rtp_transport_->SignalSentPacket.disconnect(this);
194}
195
196void BaseChannel::Init_w(webrtc::RtpTransportInternal* rtp_transport) {
197 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
198
199 network_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this, rtp_transport] {
200 SetRtpTransport(rtp_transport);
201 // Both RTP and RTCP channels should be set, we can call SetInterface on
202 // the media channel and it can set network options.
203 media_channel_->SetInterface(this);
204 });
205}
206
207void BaseChannel::Deinit() {
208 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
209 // Packets arrive on the network thread, processing packets calls virtual
210 // functions, so need to stop this process in Deinit that is called in
211 // derived classes destructor.
212 network_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
213 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
214 media_channel_->SetInterface(/*iface=*/nullptr);
215
216 if (rtp_transport_) {
217 DisconnectFromRtpTransport();
218 }
219 });
220}
221
222bool BaseChannel::SetRtpTransport(webrtc::RtpTransportInternal* rtp_transport) {
223 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
224 if (rtp_transport == rtp_transport_) {
225 return true;
226 }
227
228 if (rtp_transport_) {
229 DisconnectFromRtpTransport();
230 }
231
232 rtp_transport_ = rtp_transport;
233 if (rtp_transport_) {
234 transport_name_ = rtp_transport_->transport_name();
235
236 if (!ConnectToRtpTransport()) {
237 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to connect to the new RtpTransport for "
238 << ToString() << ".";
239 return false;
240 }
241 OnTransportReadyToSend(rtp_transport_->IsReadyToSend());
242 UpdateWritableState_n();
243
244 // Set the cached socket options.
245 for (const auto& pair : socket_options_) {
246 rtp_transport_->SetRtpOption(pair.first, pair.second);
247 }
248 if (!rtp_transport_->rtcp_mux_enabled()) {
249 for (const auto& pair : rtcp_socket_options_) {
250 rtp_transport_->SetRtcpOption(pair.first, pair.second);
251 }
252 }
253 }
254 return true;
255}
256
257void BaseChannel::Enable(bool enable) {
258 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
259
260 if (enable == enabled_s_)
261 return;
262
263 enabled_s_ = enable;
264
265 worker_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(alive_, [this, enable] {
266 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
267 // Sanity check to make sure that enabled_ and enabled_s_
268 // stay in sync.
269 RTC_DCHECK_NE(enabled_, enable);
270 if (enable) {
271 EnableMedia_w();
272 } else {
273 DisableMedia_w();
274 }
275 }));
276}

300bool BaseChannel::IsReadyToReceiveMedia_w() const {
301 // Receive data if we are enabled and have local content,
302 return enabled_ &&
303 webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(local_content_direction_);
304}
305
306bool BaseChannel::IsReadyToSendMedia_w() const {
307 // Send outgoing data if we are enabled, have local and remote content,
308 // and we have had some form of connectivity.
309 return enabled_ &&
310 webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(remote_content_direction_) &&
311 webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(local_content_direction_) &&
312 was_ever_writable();
313}

317 return SendPacket(false, packet, options);

320bool BaseChannel::SendRtcp(rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer* packet,
321 const rtc::PacketOptions& options) {
322 return SendPacket(true, packet, options);
323}
324
325int BaseChannel::SetOption(SocketType type,
326 rtc::Socket::Option opt,
327 int value) {
328 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
329 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_transport_);
330 switch (type) {
331 case ST_RTP:
332 socket_options_.push_back(
333 std::pair<rtc::Socket::Option, int>(opt, value));
334 return rtp_transport_->SetRtpOption(opt, value);
335 case ST_RTCP:
336 rtcp_socket_options_.push_back(
337 std::pair<rtc::Socket::Option, int>(opt, value));
338 return rtp_transport_->SetRtcpOption(opt, value);
339 }
340 return -1;
341}

343void BaseChannel::OnWritableState(bool writable) {
344 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
345 if (writable) {
346 ChannelWritable_n();
347 } else {
348 ChannelNotWritable_n();
349 }
350}

352void BaseChannel::OnNetworkRouteChanged(
353 absl::optional<rtc::NetworkRoute> network_route) {
354 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Network route changed for " << ToString();
355
356 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
357 rtc::NetworkRoute new_route;
358 if (network_route) {
359 new_route = *(network_route);
360 }
361 // Note: When the RTCP-muxing is not enabled, RTCP transport and RTP transport
362 // use the same transport name and MediaChannel::OnNetworkRouteChanged cannot
363 // work correctly. Intentionally leave it broken to simplify the code and
364 // encourage the users to stop using non-muxing RTCP.
365 media_channel_->OnNetworkRouteChanged(transport_name_, new_route);
366}

371 RTC_DCHECK(!on_first_packet_received_ || !callback);
372 on_first_packet_received_ = std::move(callback);
373}

380bool BaseChannel::SendPacket(bool rtcp,
381 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer* packet,
382 const rtc::PacketOptions& options) {
383 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
384 // Until all the code is migrated to use RtpPacketType instead of bool.
385 RtpPacketType packet_type = rtcp ? RtpPacketType::kRtcp : RtpPacketType::kRtp;
386 // SendPacket gets called from MediaEngine, on a pacer or an encoder thread.
387 // If the thread is not our network thread, we will post to our network
388 // so that the real work happens on our network. This avoids us having to
389 // synchronize access to all the pieces of the send path, including
390 // SRTP and the inner workings of the transport channels.
391 // The only downside is that we can't return a proper failure code if
392 // needed. Since UDP is unreliable anyway, this should be a non-issue.
393
394 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "BaseChannel::SendPacket");
395
396 // Now that we are on the correct thread, ensure we have a place to send this
397 // packet before doing anything. (We might get RTCP packets that we don't
398 // intend to send.) If we've negotiated RTCP mux, send RTCP over the RTP
399 // transport.
400 if (!rtp_transport_ || !rtp_transport_->IsWritable(rtcp)) {
401 return false;
402 }
403
404 // Protect ourselves against crazy data.
405 if (!IsValidRtpPacketSize(packet_type, packet->size())) {
406 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Dropping outgoing " << ToString() << " "
407 << RtpPacketTypeToString(packet_type)
408 << " packet: wrong size=" << packet->size();
409 return false;
410 }
411
412 if (!srtp_active()) {
413 if (srtp_required_) {
414 // The audio/video engines may attempt to send RTCP packets as soon as the
415 // streams are created, so don't treat this as an error for RTCP.
416 // See: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=6809
417 if (rtcp) {
418 return false;
419 }
420 // However, there shouldn't be any RTP packets sent before SRTP is set up
421 // (and SetSend(true) is called).
422 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Can't send outgoing RTP packet for " << ToString()
423 << " when SRTP is inactive and crypto is required";
424 RTC_NOTREACHED();
425 return false;
426 }
427
428 std::string packet_type = rtcp ? "RTCP" : "RTP";
429 RTC_DLOG(LS_WARNING) << "Sending an " << packet_type
430 << " packet without encryption for " << ToString()
431 << ".";
432 }
433
434 // Bon voyage.
435 return rtcp ? rtp_transport_->SendRtcpPacket(packet, options, PF_SRTP_BYPASS)
436 : rtp_transport_->SendRtpPacket(packet, options, PF_SRTP_BYPASS);
437}
438
439void BaseChannel::OnRtpPacket(const webrtc::RtpPacketReceived& parsed_packet) {
440 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
441
442 if (on_first_packet_received_) {
443 on_first_packet_received_();
444 on_first_packet_received_ = nullptr;
445 }
446
447 if (!srtp_active() && srtp_required_) {
448 // Our session description indicates that SRTP is required, but we got a
449 // packet before our SRTP filter is active. This means either that
450 // a) we got SRTP packets before we received the SDES keys, in which case
451 // we can't decrypt it anyway, or
452 // b) we got SRTP packets before DTLS completed on both the RTP and RTCP
453 // transports, so we haven't yet extracted keys, even if DTLS did
454 // complete on the transport that the packets are being sent on. It's
455 // really good practice to wait for both RTP and RTCP to be good to go
456 // before sending media, to prevent weird failure modes, so it's fine
457 // for us to just eat packets here. This is all sidestepped if RTCP mux
458 // is used anyway.
459 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Can't process incoming RTP packet when "
460 "SRTP is inactive and crypto is required "
461 << ToString();
462 return;
463 }
464
465 webrtc::Timestamp packet_time = parsed_packet.arrival_time();
466 media_channel_->OnPacketReceived(
467 parsed_packet.Buffer(),
468 packet_time.IsMinusInfinity() ? -1 : packet_time.us());
469}
470
471void BaseChannel::UpdateRtpHeaderExtensionMap(
472 const RtpHeaderExtensions& header_extensions) {
473 // Update the header extension map on network thread in case there is data
474 // race.
475 //
476 // NOTE: This doesn't take the BUNDLE case in account meaning the RTP header
477 // extension maps are not merged when BUNDLE is enabled. This is fine because
478 // the ID for MID should be consistent among all the RTP transports.
479 network_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this, &header_extensions] {
480 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
481 rtp_transport_->UpdateRtpHeaderExtensionMap(header_extensions);
482 });
483}
484
485bool BaseChannel::RegisterRtpDemuxerSink_w() {
486 if (demuxer_criteria_ == previous_demuxer_criteria_) {
487 return true;
488 }
489 media_channel_->OnDemuxerCriteriaUpdatePending();
490 // Copy demuxer criteria, since they're a worker-thread variable
491 // and we want to pass them to the network thread
492 return network_thread_->Invoke<bool>(
493 RTC_FROM_HERE, [this, demuxer_criteria = demuxer_criteria_] {
494 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
495 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_transport_);
496 bool result =
497 rtp_transport_->RegisterRtpDemuxerSink(demuxer_criteria, this);
498 if (result) {
499 previous_demuxer_criteria_ = demuxer_criteria;
500 } else {
501 previous_demuxer_criteria_ = {};
502 }
503 media_channel_->OnDemuxerCriteriaUpdateComplete();
504 return result;
505 });
506}

508void BaseChannel::EnableMedia_w() {
509 if (enabled_)
510 return;
511
512 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Channel enabled: " << ToString();
513 enabled_ = true;
514 UpdateMediaSendRecvState_w();
515}

517void BaseChannel::DisableMedia_w() {
518 if (!enabled_)
519 return;
520
521 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Channel disabled: " << ToString();
522 enabled_ = false;
523 UpdateMediaSendRecvState_w();
524}
525
526void BaseChannel::UpdateWritableState_n() {
527 if (rtp_transport_->IsWritable(/*rtcp=*/true) &&
528 rtp_transport_->IsWritable(/*rtcp=*/false)) {
529 ChannelWritable_n();
530 } else {
531 ChannelNotWritable_n();
532 }
533}
534
535void BaseChannel::ChannelWritable_n() {
536 if (writable_) {
537 return;
538 }
539 writable_ = true;
540 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Channel writable (" << ToString() << ")"
541 << (was_ever_writable_n_ ? "" : " for the first time");
542 // We only have to do this PostTask once, when first transitioning to
543 // writable.
544 if (!was_ever_writable_n_) {
545 worker_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(alive_, [this] {
546 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
547 was_ever_writable_ = true;
548 UpdateMediaSendRecvState_w();
549 }));
550 }
551 was_ever_writable_n_ = true;
552}
553
554void BaseChannel::ChannelNotWritable_n() {
555 if (!writable_) {
556 return;
557 }
558 writable_ = false;
559 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Channel not writable (" << ToString() << ")";
560}

573
574bool BaseChannel::SetPayloadTypeDemuxingEnabled_w(bool enabled) {
575 if (enabled == payload_type_demuxing_enabled_) {
576 return true;
577 }
578 payload_type_demuxing_enabled_ = enabled;
579 if (!enabled) {
580 // TODO(crbug.com/11477): This will remove *all* unsignaled streams (those
581 // without an explicitly signaled SSRC), which may include streams that
582 // were matched to this channel by MID or RID. Ideally we'd remove only the
583 // streams that were matched based on payload type alone, but currently
584 // there is no straightforward way to identify those streams.
585 media_channel()->ResetUnsignaledRecvStream();
586 demuxer_criteria_.payload_types.clear();
587 if (!RegisterRtpDemuxerSink_w()) {
588 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to disable payload type demuxing for "
589 << ToString();
590 return false;
591 }
592 } else if (!payload_types_.empty()) {
593 demuxer_criteria_.payload_types.insert(payload_types_.begin(),
594 payload_types_.end());
595 if (!RegisterRtpDemuxerSink_w()) {
596 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to enable payload type demuxing for "
597 << ToString();
598 return false;
599 }
600 }
601 return true;
602}
603
604bool BaseChannel::UpdateLocalStreams_w(const std::vector<StreamParams>& streams,
605 SdpType type,
606 std::string* error_desc) {
607 // In the case of RIDs (where SSRCs are not negotiated), this method will
608 // generate an SSRC for each layer in StreamParams. That representation will
609 // be stored internally in |local_streams_|.
610 // In subsequent offers, the same stream can appear in |streams| again
611 // (without the SSRCs), so it should be looked up using RIDs (if available)
612 // and then by primary SSRC.
613 // In both scenarios, it is safe to assume that the media channel will be
614 // created with a StreamParams object with SSRCs. However, it is not safe to
615 // assume that |local_streams_| will always have SSRCs as there are scenarios
616 // in which niether SSRCs or RIDs are negotiated.
617
618 // Check for streams that have been removed.
619 bool ret = true;
620 for (const StreamParams& old_stream : local_streams_) {
621 if (!old_stream.has_ssrcs() ||
622 GetStream(streams, StreamFinder(&old_stream))) {
623 continue;
624 }
625 if (!media_channel()->RemoveSendStream(old_stream.first_ssrc())) {
626 rtc::StringBuilder desc;
627 desc << "Failed to remove send stream with ssrc "
628 << old_stream.first_ssrc() << " from m-section with mid='"
629 << content_name() << "'.";
630 SafeSetError(desc.str(), error_desc);
631 ret = false;
632 }
633 }
634 // Check for new streams.
635 std::vector<StreamParams> all_streams;
636 for (const StreamParams& stream : streams) {
637 StreamParams* existing = GetStream(local_streams_, StreamFinder(&stream));
638 if (existing) {
639 // Parameters cannot change for an existing stream.
640 all_streams.push_back(*existing);
641 continue;
642 }
643
644 all_streams.push_back(stream);
645 StreamParams& new_stream = all_streams.back();
646
647 if (!new_stream.has_ssrcs() && !new_stream.has_rids()) {
648 continue;
649 }
650
651 RTC_DCHECK(new_stream.has_ssrcs() || new_stream.has_rids());
652 if (new_stream.has_ssrcs() && new_stream.has_rids()) {
653 rtc::StringBuilder desc;
654 desc << "Failed to add send stream: " << new_stream.first_ssrc()
655 << " into m-section with mid='" << content_name()
656 << "'. Stream has both SSRCs and RIDs.";
657 SafeSetError(desc.str(), error_desc);
658 ret = false;
659 continue;
660 }
661
662 // At this point we use the legacy simulcast group in StreamParams to
663 // indicate that we want multiple layers to the media channel.
664 if (!new_stream.has_ssrcs()) {
665 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10250): Indicate if flex is desired here.
666 new_stream.GenerateSsrcs(new_stream.rids().size(), /* rtx = */ true,
667 /* flex_fec = */ false, ssrc_generator_);
668 }
669
670 if (media_channel()->AddSendStream(new_stream)) {
671 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Add send stream ssrc: " << new_stream.ssrcs[0]
672 << " into " << ToString();
673 } else {
674 rtc::StringBuilder desc;
675 desc << "Failed to add send stream ssrc: " << new_stream.first_ssrc()
676 << " into m-section with mid='" << content_name() << "'";
677 SafeSetError(desc.str(), error_desc);
678 ret = false;
679 }
680 }
681 local_streams_ = all_streams;
682 return ret;
683}
684
685bool BaseChannel::UpdateRemoteStreams_w(
686 const std::vector<StreamParams>& streams,
687 SdpType type,
688 std::string* error_desc) {
689 // Check for streams that have been removed.
690 bool ret = true;
691 for (const StreamParams& old_stream : remote_streams_) {
692 // If we no longer have an unsignaled stream, we would like to remove
693 // the unsignaled stream params that are cached.
694 if (!old_stream.has_ssrcs() && !HasStreamWithNoSsrcs(streams)) {
695 ResetUnsignaledRecvStream_w();
696 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Reset unsignaled remote stream for " << ToString()
697 << ".";
698 } else if (old_stream.has_ssrcs() &&
699 !GetStreamBySsrc(streams, old_stream.first_ssrc())) {
700 if (RemoveRecvStream_w(old_stream.first_ssrc())) {
701 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Remove remote ssrc: " << old_stream.first_ssrc()
702 << " from " << ToString() << ".";
703 } else {
704 rtc::StringBuilder desc;
705 desc << "Failed to remove remote stream with ssrc "
706 << old_stream.first_ssrc() << " from m-section with mid='"
707 << content_name() << "'.";
708 SafeSetError(desc.str(), error_desc);
709 ret = false;
710 }
711 }
712 }
713 demuxer_criteria_.ssrcs.clear();
714 // Check for new streams.
715 for (const StreamParams& new_stream : streams) {
716 // We allow a StreamParams with an empty list of SSRCs, in which case the
717 // MediaChannel will cache the parameters and use them for any unsignaled
718 // stream received later.
719 if ((!new_stream.has_ssrcs() && !HasStreamWithNoSsrcs(remote_streams_)) ||
720 !GetStreamBySsrc(remote_streams_, new_stream.first_ssrc())) {
721 if (AddRecvStream_w(new_stream)) {
722 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Add remote ssrc: "
723 << (new_stream.has_ssrcs()
724 ? std::to_string(new_stream.first_ssrc())
725 : "unsignaled")
726 << " to " << ToString();
727 } else {
728 rtc::StringBuilder desc;
729 desc << "Failed to add remote stream ssrc: "
730 << (new_stream.has_ssrcs()
731 ? std::to_string(new_stream.first_ssrc())
732 : "unsignaled")
733 << " to " << ToString();
734 SafeSetError(desc.str(), error_desc);
735 ret = false;
736 }
737 }
738 // Update the receiving SSRCs.
739 demuxer_criteria_.ssrcs.insert(new_stream.ssrcs.begin(),
740 new_stream.ssrcs.end());
741 }
742 // Re-register the sink to update the receiving ssrcs.
743 if (!RegisterRtpDemuxerSink_w()) {
744 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to set up demuxing for " << ToString();
745 ret = false;
746 }
747 remote_streams_ = streams;
748 return ret;
749}
750
751RtpHeaderExtensions BaseChannel::GetFilteredRtpHeaderExtensions(
752 const RtpHeaderExtensions& extensions) {
753 if (crypto_options_.srtp.enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions) {
754 RtpHeaderExtensions filtered;
755 absl::c_copy_if(extensions, std::back_inserter(filtered),
756 [](const webrtc::RtpExtension& extension) {
757 return !extension.encrypt;
758 });
759 return filtered;
760 }
761
762 return webrtc::RtpExtension::FilterDuplicateNonEncrypted(extensions);
763}
764
765void BaseChannel::MaybeAddHandledPayloadType(int payload_type) {
766 if (payload_type_demuxing_enabled_) {
767 demuxer_criteria_.payload_types.insert(static_cast<uint8_t>(payload_type));
768 }
769 // Even if payload type demuxing is currently disabled, we need to remember
770 // the payload types in case it's re-enabled later.
771 payload_types_.insert(static_cast<uint8_t>(payload_type));
772}
773
774void BaseChannel::ClearHandledPayloadTypes() {
775 demuxer_criteria_.payload_types.clear();
776 payload_types_.clear();
777}

779void BaseChannel::SignalSentPacket_n(const rtc::SentPacket& sent_packet) {
780 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
781 media_channel()->OnPacketSent(sent_packet);
782}

808void VoiceChannel::UpdateMediaSendRecvState_w() {
809 // Render incoming data if we're the active call, and we have the local
810 // content. We receive data on the default channel and multiplexed streams.
811 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
812 bool recv = IsReadyToReceiveMedia_w();
813 media_channel()->SetPlayout(recv);
814
815 // Send outgoing data if we're the active call, we have the remote content,
816 // and we have had some form of connectivity.
817 bool send = IsReadyToSendMedia_w();
818 media_channel()->SetSend(send);
819
820 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing voice state, recv=" << recv << " send=" << send
821 << " for " << ToString();
822}

824bool VoiceChannel::SetLocalContent_w(const MediaContentDescription* content,
825 SdpType type,
826 std::string* error_desc) {
827 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VoiceChannel::SetLocalContent_w");
828 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
829 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Setting local voice description for " << ToString();
830
831 RtpHeaderExtensions rtp_header_extensions =
832 GetFilteredRtpHeaderExtensions(content->rtp_header_extensions());
833 // TODO(tommi): There's a hop to the network thread here.
834 // some of the below is also network thread related.
835 UpdateRtpHeaderExtensionMap(rtp_header_extensions);
836 media_channel()->SetExtmapAllowMixed(content->extmap_allow_mixed());
837
838 AudioRecvParameters recv_params = last_recv_params_;
839 RtpParametersFromMediaDescription(
840 content->as_audio(), rtp_header_extensions,
841 webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(content->direction()),
842 &recv_params);
843
844 if (!media_channel()->SetRecvParameters(recv_params)) {
845 SafeSetError(
846 "Failed to set local audio description recv parameters for m-section "
847 "with mid='" +
848 content_name() + "'.",
849 error_desc);
850 return false;
851 }
852
853 if (webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(content->direction())) {
854 for (const AudioCodec& codec : content->as_audio()->codecs()) {
855 MaybeAddHandledPayloadType(codec.id);
856 }
857 // Need to re-register the sink to update the handled payload.
858 if (!RegisterRtpDemuxerSink_w()) {
859 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to set up audio demuxing for " << ToString();
860 return false;
861 }
862 }
863
864 last_recv_params_ = recv_params;
865
866 // TODO(pthatcher): Move local streams into AudioSendParameters, and
867 // only give it to the media channel once we have a remote
868 // description too (without a remote description, we won't be able
869 // to send them anyway).
870 if (!UpdateLocalStreams_w(content->as_audio()->streams(), type, error_desc)) {
871 SafeSetError(
872 "Failed to set local audio description streams for m-section with "
873 "mid='" +
874 content_name() + "'.",
875 error_desc);
876 return false;
877 }
878
879 set_local_content_direction(content->direction());
880 UpdateMediaSendRecvState_w();
881 return true;
882}
883
884bool VoiceChannel::SetRemoteContent_w(const MediaContentDescription* content,
885 SdpType type,
886 std::string* error_desc) {
887 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VoiceChannel::SetRemoteContent_w");
888 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
889 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Setting remote voice description for " << ToString();
890
891 const AudioContentDescription* audio = content->as_audio();
892
893 RtpHeaderExtensions rtp_header_extensions =
894 GetFilteredRtpHeaderExtensions(audio->rtp_header_extensions());
895
896 AudioSendParameters send_params = last_send_params_;
897 RtpSendParametersFromMediaDescription(
898 audio, rtp_header_extensions,
899 webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(audio->direction()), &send_params);
900 send_params.mid = content_name();
901
902 bool parameters_applied = media_channel()->SetSendParameters(send_params);
903 if (!parameters_applied) {
904 SafeSetError(
905 "Failed to set remote audio description send parameters for m-section "
906 "with mid='" +
907 content_name() + "'.",
908 error_desc);
909 return false;
910 }
911 last_send_params_ = send_params;
912
913 if (!webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(content->direction())) {
914 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "SetRemoteContent_w: remote side will not send - "
915 "disable payload type demuxing for "
916 << ToString();
917 ClearHandledPayloadTypes();
918 if (!RegisterRtpDemuxerSink_w()) {
919 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to update audio demuxing for " << ToString();
920 return false;
921 }
922 }
923
924 // TODO(pthatcher): Move remote streams into AudioRecvParameters,
925 // and only give it to the media channel once we have a local
926 // description too (without a local description, we won't be able to
927 // recv them anyway).
928 if (!UpdateRemoteStreams_w(audio->streams(), type, error_desc)) {
929 SafeSetError(
930 "Failed to set remote audio description streams for m-section with "
931 "mid='" +
932 content_name() + "'.",
933 error_desc);
934 return false;
935 }
936
937 set_remote_content_direction(content->direction());
938 UpdateMediaSendRecvState_w();
939 return true;
940}

986bool VideoChannel::SetLocalContent_w(const MediaContentDescription* content,
987 SdpType type,
988 std::string* error_desc) {
989 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VideoChannel::SetLocalContent_w");
990 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
991 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Setting local video description for " << ToString();
992
993 RtpHeaderExtensions rtp_header_extensions =
994 GetFilteredRtpHeaderExtensions(content->rtp_header_extensions());
995 UpdateRtpHeaderExtensionMap(rtp_header_extensions);
996 media_channel()->SetExtmapAllowMixed(content->extmap_allow_mixed());
997
998 VideoRecvParameters recv_params = last_recv_params_;
999
1000 RtpParametersFromMediaDescription(
1001 content->as_video(), rtp_header_extensions,
1002 webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(content->direction()),
1003 &recv_params);
1004
1005 VideoSendParameters send_params = last_send_params_;
1006
1007 bool needs_send_params_update = false;
1008 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer || type == SdpType::kPrAnswer) {
1009 for (auto& send_codec : send_params.codecs) {
1010 auto* recv_codec = FindMatchingCodec(recv_params.codecs, send_codec);
1011 if (recv_codec) {
1012 if (!recv_codec->packetization && send_codec.packetization) {
1013 send_codec.packetization.reset();
1014 needs_send_params_update = true;
1015 } else if (recv_codec->packetization != send_codec.packetization) {
1016 SafeSetError(
1017 "Failed to set local answer due to invalid codec packetization "
1018 "specified in m-section with mid='" +
1019 content_name() + "'.",
1020 error_desc);
1021 return false;
1022 }
1023 }
1024 }
1025 }
1026
1027 if (!media_channel()->SetRecvParameters(recv_params)) {
1028 SafeSetError(
1029 "Failed to set local video description recv parameters for m-section "
1030 "with mid='" +
1031 content_name() + "'.",
1032 error_desc);
1033 return false;
1034 }
1035
1036 if (webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(content->direction())) {
1037 for (const VideoCodec& codec : content->as_video()->codecs()) {
1038 MaybeAddHandledPayloadType(codec.id);
1039 }
1040 // Need to re-register the sink to update the handled payload.
1041 if (!RegisterRtpDemuxerSink_w()) {
1042 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to set up video demuxing for " << ToString();
1043 return false;
1044 }
1045 }
1046
1047 last_recv_params_ = recv_params;
1048
1049 if (needs_send_params_update) {
1050 if (!media_channel()->SetSendParameters(send_params)) {
1051 SafeSetError("Failed to set send parameters for m-section with mid='" +
1052 content_name() + "'.",
1053 error_desc);
1054 return false;
1055 }
1056 last_send_params_ = send_params;
1057 }
1058
1059 // TODO(pthatcher): Move local streams into VideoSendParameters, and
1060 // only give it to the media channel once we have a remote
1061 // description too (without a remote description, we won't be able
1062 // to send them anyway).
1063 if (!UpdateLocalStreams_w(content->as_video()->streams(), type, error_desc)) {
1064 SafeSetError(
1065 "Failed to set local video description streams for m-section with "
1066 "mid='" +
1067 content_name() + "'.",
1068 error_desc);
1069 return false;
1070 }
1071
1072 set_local_content_direction(content->direction());
1073 UpdateMediaSendRecvState_w();
1074 return true;
1075}

1077bool VideoChannel::SetRemoteContent_w(const MediaContentDescription* content,
1078 SdpType type,
1079 std::string* error_desc) {
1080 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VideoChannel::SetRemoteContent_w");
1081 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
1082 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Setting remote video description for " << ToString();
1083
1084 const VideoContentDescription* video = content->as_video();
1085
1086 RtpHeaderExtensions rtp_header_extensions =
1087 GetFilteredRtpHeaderExtensions(video->rtp_header_extensions());
1088
1089 VideoSendParameters send_params = last_send_params_;
1090 RtpSendParametersFromMediaDescription(
1091 video, rtp_header_extensions,
1092 webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(video->direction()), &send_params);
1093 if (video->conference_mode()) {
1094 send_params.conference_mode = true;
1095 }
1096 send_params.mid = content_name();
1097
1098 VideoRecvParameters recv_params = last_recv_params_;
1099
1100 bool needs_recv_params_update = false;
1101 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer || type == SdpType::kPrAnswer) {
1102 for (auto& recv_codec : recv_params.codecs) {
1103 auto* send_codec = FindMatchingCodec(send_params.codecs, recv_codec);
1104 if (send_codec) {
1105 if (!send_codec->packetization && recv_codec.packetization) {
1106 recv_codec.packetization.reset();
1107 needs_recv_params_update = true;
1108 } else if (send_codec->packetization != recv_codec.packetization) {
1109 SafeSetError(
1110 "Failed to set remote answer due to invalid codec packetization "
1111 "specifid in m-section with mid='" +
1112 content_name() + "'.",
1113 error_desc);
1114 return false;
1115 }
1116 }
1117 }
1118 }
1119
1120 if (!media_channel()->SetSendParameters(send_params)) {
1121 SafeSetError(
1122 "Failed to set remote video description send parameters for m-section "
1123 "with mid='" +
1124 content_name() + "'.",
1125 error_desc);
1126 return false;
1127 }
1128 last_send_params_ = send_params;
1129
1130 if (needs_recv_params_update) {
1131 if (!media_channel()->SetRecvParameters(recv_params)) {
1132 SafeSetError("Failed to set recv parameters for m-section with mid='" +
1133 content_name() + "'.",
1134 error_desc);
1135 return false;
1136 }
1137 last_recv_params_ = recv_params;
1138 }
1139
1140 if (!webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(content->direction())) {
1141 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "SetRemoteContent_w: remote side will not send - "
1142 "disable payload type demuxing for "
1143 << ToString();
1144 ClearHandledPayloadTypes();
1145 if (!RegisterRtpDemuxerSink_w()) {
1146 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to update video demuxing for " << ToString();
1147 return false;
1148 }
1149 }
1150
1151 // TODO(pthatcher): Move remote streams into VideoRecvParameters,
1152 // and only give it to the media channel once we have a local
1153 // description too (without a local description, we won't be able to
1154 // recv them anyway).
1155 if (!UpdateRemoteStreams_w(video->streams(), type, error_desc)) {
1156 SafeSetError(
1157 "Failed to set remote video description streams for m-section with "
1158 "mid='" +
1159 content_name() + "'.",
1160 error_desc);
1161 return false;
1162 }
1163 set_remote_content_direction(content->direction());
1164 UpdateMediaSendRecvState_w();
1165 return true;
1166}
